==English==

===Proper noun===
'''Mbabaram'''
# '''Mbabaram''' ([[ISO]] language code: QLD) is an [[ergative]] [[Australian]] [[aboriginal]] language of the Southern Pama branch of the large [[Pama-Nyungan]] family of languages.  As of 1981, only two speakers of Mbabaram remained in northern [[Queensland]], [[Australia]].

===Alternative spellings===
Mbara, Barbaram, Barbarem, Bar-barum, Balbarum, Boobu-ram, Mogmbabarum, Umbarbarem, Oombarbarum, Wumbabaram, Woombarbarram, Woombarrmbarra.

